FBIS4-53568 "dreas098_a_94023" FBIS-EAS-94-098 Daily Report 20 May 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Watanabe on Postponing Redistricting Effort Watanabe on Postponing Redistricting Effort OW2005081794 Tokyo KYODO in English 0735 GMT 20 May 94 OW2005081794 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Fukuoka, May 20 KYODO -- A senior member of the coalition government's core party said Friday [20 May] it is possible to postpone enacting a bill on redistricting single-seat constituencies until an extraordinary Diet session in autumn. Kozo Watanabe, acting secretary general of Shinseito [Japan Renewal Party], said at a speech in Fukuoka that the postponement is possible if the ruling and opposition parties agree to discuss the matter.
